// === AUTO-GENERATED FROM tradingview/occurrence_matrix.pine ===
// Ticker group: G4 · baseline tol only
// DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY. Re-generate with:
//   python scripts/build_om_slices.py
// ================================================================
// max_bars_back=210: caps history retention to ~210 bars per series reference.
// SMA200 needs the deepest lookback (200 bars); the state machine only uses
// [1] refs. Default is 1500 — which times 725 state machines × multiple [1]
// refs each = the "Memory limits exceeded" runtime error. 210 is enough for
// all indicators here and reduces memory ~7x.
indicator("Occurrence Matrix [ST] — G4 t25-32", shorttitle="OM G4 t25-32", overlay=true, max_bars_back=210)

string ver_num  = "v15.0-BAND-g4"
string ver_date = "2026-07-08"
// v15.0-BAND: classification is now BAND-ZONE v2 (band = k*ATR, absolute; approved by CZ). run_sm was
//        the old far-edge+timer machine with a percent band; it is replaced by the "fat MA" model
//        (reach the band = bounce; pass the far edge = false/break), counting a bounce per rejection
//        (re-armed) — validated in scripts/occurrence_band_sm.py + test_occurrence_band.py (26/26).
//        Band source = kBand*ta.atr(bandN) per security. get_tol_grid() is kept ONLY to mask skipped
//        cells (its % value is no longer the band). CSV/snapshot schema, slicer, parser, API and the
//        dashboard are UNCHANGED (same 140-int layout; app still reads the baseline block).
// v14.0: +2 levels Bollinger Bands (BB Upper/Lower, 20,2σ) → 7 levels/ticker;
//        +3 tickers SMH, EWY, DRAM (Sector/Country ETFs) → 32 tickers.
//        Snapshot schema v14: ma=[9,20,50,200,"vwap","bb_u","bb_l"], 140 ints/ticker
//        (5 tol × 7 levels × 4 metrics). Memory: run the g1/g2 TICKER-GROUP files
//        (baseline tol, 16 tickers each) generated by scripts/build_om_slices.py,
//        then `om_paste_snapshot.py --merge-tickers`. This master is the source of
//        truth for that generator (running the master itself will exceed memory).

